title: Claude Monet Vetheuil Unmatted Print
description:
Print developed from Claude Monet’s Vetheuil, 1901, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Claude Monet’s series of 15 canvases depicting the village of Vétheuil, 7 miles from his home in Giverny, dates from July 1901. The Vétheuil series shows the view across the river from Monet’s balcony at various times of day.

  • Print Reproduction
  • Image size:  10 x 9.625 in.
  • Full poster size: 11 x 14 in.
  • Materials: Premium Cardstock
